        {
            "_id": "tOytzXzmH37Ilg3b",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/action.svg",
            "name": "Join Us!",
            "sort": 500000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "action"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": 2
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>The ghostly guest Flies over to a space adjacent to a creature, then extends their arms in an invitation to join the ghost in whatever form of revelry it appears to be engaged in at the moment, be it dancing, drinking, or eating. The target must attempt a @Check[will|dc:24] save to resist the invitation. On a failed save, roll [[/gmr 1d6#Revelry]] to determine what the ghost's current revelry is and what effect the creature endures. If the target fails its save against Join Us! while already enduring a condition inflicted by a previous failed save, the new condition replaces the old condition, and the change in condition leaves the character @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Off-Guard] for 1 round from the disorienting sensations.</p>\n<p><strong>1–2 Dancing</strong> The creature suddenly feels as if they've been dancing the night away. Aches and pains settle into their bodies, and they become @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Enfeebled]{Enfeebled 1} (@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Enfeebled]{Enfeebled 2} on a critical failure) for 1 hour.</p>\n<p><strong>3–4 Drinking</strong> The creature suddenly feels dizzy and drunk and becomes @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Stupefied]{Stupefied 1} (@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Stupefied]{Stupefied 2} on a critical failure) for 1 hour.</p>\n<p><strong>5–6 Eating</strong> The creature suddenly feels bloated and overfull and becomes @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Clumsy]{Clumsy 1} (@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Clumsy]{Clumsy 2} on a critical failure) for 1 hour.</p>"
                },
